# Unordered List Marker Positioning

- **Default behavior**: Use outside markers so wrapped lines align with the list content, not under the bullet.
- **Tailwind utilities**: Prefer `list-disc list-outside pl-5` (adjust padding per context). Avoid `list-inside` unless thereâ€™s a strong visual reason.
- **Consistency**: Apply the same pattern to nested lists; add incremental padding (e.g., `pl-4` per level) while keeping `list-outside`.
- **Prose blocks**: If using typography utilities, ensure ULs still use outside markers. Override when necessary (e.g., `prose-ul:list-outside`).
- **Exceptions (rare)**: Only use `list-inside` in tight UI where markers must sit in-column and wrapping under the marker is explicitly desired.

## Examples

### Before (not preferred)
```astro
<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm">
  <li>
    Long line that wraps onto multiple lines. Subsequent lines sit under the bullet, which hurts scanability.
  </li>
  <li>Another item</li>
  <li>Third item</li>
</ul>
```

### After (preferred)
```astro
<ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-5 text-sm">
  <li>
    Long line that wraps onto multiple lines. Subsequent lines align with the content, not under the bullet.
  </li>
  <li>Another item</li>
  <li>Third item</li>
  <!-- Nested list example -->
  <li>
    Parent item
    <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-4">
      <li>Nested item</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  
```

## Rationale

- **Scanability**: Aligning wrapped lines with the content column keeps bullets as markers, not layout anchors.
- **Consistency**: Avoids unexpected text creep under markers across components and pages.
- **Flexibility**: Padding (`pl-*`) can be tuned per layout without sacrificing alignment.

